## CodeRabbit AI Code Review

This project includes [CodeRabbit](https://coderabbit.ai) configuration for AI-powered code reviews.

### Features

- **Automated PR Reviews** — AI reviews every pull request
- **Clean Architecture Checks** — Validates dependency rule compliance
- **Path-Specific Instructions** — Tailored review for each layer
- **Breaking Change Detection** — Identifies API breaking changes
- **Code Quality Tools** — Integrated Ruff, Biome, ShellCheck, etc.

### Configuration

The `.coderabbit.yaml` file includes:

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `reviews.path_instructions` | Layer-specific Clean Architecture rules |
| `reviews.path_filters` | Exclude generated/vendored files |
| `reviews.labeling_instructions` | Auto-label PRs by type |
| `reviews.tools` | Enable/disable linting tools |
| `reviews.finishing_touches` | Auto-generate docstrings, tests |
| `reviews.pre_merge_checks` | Quality gates before merge |

### Commands

Interact with CodeRabbit in PR comments:

| Command | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `@coderabbitai summary` | Generate PR summary |
| `@coderabbitai review` | Request full review |
| `@coderabbitai resolve` | Resolve all threads |
| `@coderabbitai ignore` | Ignore file/path |
| `@coderabbitai help` | Show all commands |

### Customizing Reviews

Add path-specific instructions in `.coderabbit.yaml`:

```yaml
reviews:
  path_instructions:
    - path: "backend/src/my_module/**"
      instructions: |
        This module handles X. Review for:
        - Y patterns
        - Z constraints
```

### Disabling for Specific PRs

Add to PR title or body:
- `[skip review]` — Skip CodeRabbit review entirely
- `WIP` or `DRAFT` — Skip review for work-in-progress

### Free Tier Limitations

CodeRabbit free tier includes:
- Unlimited public repositories
- AI-powered code reviews
- Basic tool integrations
- Community support

For private repos or advanced features, see [CodeRabbit pricing](https://coderabbit.ai/pricing).
